          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td>
      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
        <tr>
          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Arundel Mills, Maryland 6/8/2002<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.33)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=8935'>Chris "Raywind" Slye</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=8935&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 8, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Back yet again, for our bi-weekly installment of tournament reports..<br>
<br>
It&#39;s the same as usual, 4-round swiss, good attendance.<br>
<br>
Satisfied with my vacation, I went back to my tried and true Underneath deck, much to my relief. (And the chagrin of others)<br>
<br>
Round 1: Radget-Gyrg-Fossik:R vs Culla-Yericho-?<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, as I was last time, I was paired with a player pretty new to the game. We started off with him winning the die roll, and electing to go second.. Radget came out with her trusty Giant Parmalag, and it&#39;s Crystal brother... Refreshing one, I ended my turn. On his turn, he brought out Culla, a Stalker&#39;s Boots, and then summoned a pair of creatures. Back to Radget again, she slipped on a pair of Strag&#39;s Claws, refreshed one of her buddies, and went to town on those nasty jungle-beasties. It went on like this for a few more turns, as Radget&#39;s hordes ripped through the opposing Magi..<br>
<br>
Results: 1 - 0<br>
<br>
Round 2: Me vs Warrada-Togoth-Zet<br>
<br>
I went first again, putting out a pair of creatures before ending my turn.. My opponant brought Warrada out, with all five of her starting cards, somewhat to my surprise. After pondering for a bit, he used the Tomes to research an Entomb, which he applied to a Cataclysm, which wiped my side of the board out. With only a Gorath in hand, and not enough energy to play it, he finished. I realize now, Cataclysm should&#39;ve taken out the Ring and the Tomes.. Argh.. with two Core matches tonight, my brain&#39;s fried.. Suffice to say, I took out Warrada and Togoth at the cost of Radget. Just before I defeated Togoth, I added insult to injury by Resonating his Grim Goblet, and discarding his hand. Zet took revenge, however, by Turning my injured Akkar, and using his power on my Cave Rudwot. Left with just 8 energy after energizing, Gyrg sacrificed himself to Thunderquake his own stolen creatures, leaving Zet with little energy. When Fossik took over, he took one look at Zet and knocked the lightweight over.<br>
<br>
Results: 2 - 0<br>
<br>
Round 3: Me vs Iain-?-? (It&#39;s kinda hard to remember Magi who flip by so fast.. )<br>
<br>
Radget went first again, setting out a Cave Rudwot, her Giant Parmalag, and an Arboll for fun.. Saccing the Arboll for the Rudwot, she refreshed the Parmalag, and finished her turn.. Her opponant? Iain.. How I hate Iain.. Luckily, both of my creatures were above their starting energies, so after a Beginning&#39;s End, and an Ambush to each, I still had a 4e Rudwot, and a 3e GP. Iain then summoned a 10e Paradywn creature, warped down to 9, leaving him with nothing at all. So, what&#39;d I do? Shockwave it, of course! Radget took out the next Magi as well, then Gyrg finished up the third Magi..<br>
<br>
Results: 3 - 0<br>
<br>
Round 4: Me vs Ogar-King Korg-Morag<br>
<br>
Ogar was annoying.. King Korg was smitten by an Athik, and Morag was pummled by Parmalags. There was one rather heart-stopping moment, when I brought Fossik out, and spent all his energy on a Tunnel Parmalag, an Athik, and a Parmalag.. I figure to myself.. &quot;Core dosn&#39;t have any mass removal..&quot; and then, as soon as I turns over his next Magi, I think, in utter horror.. &quot;HARROR!&quot;.. Luckily, it was just Morag.<br>
<br>
Results: 4 - 0<br>
<br>
So, I ended up winning again, yup. Got a nifty Orothe poster this time, which I traded for the Cald one I had won previously. See.. I traded the Cald for a stack of Underneath foils, then traded the Orothe for Cald. Trust me, it works out.<br>
<br>
I&#39;ll post up this deck in the next couple of days..<br>
 <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/magination/treports/treports.php?id=3719&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/magination/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></td></tr></table></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
